                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>Facebook’s growing market power should be concerning, especially for younger generations that are dependent on it. As noted in the hearings, finding the right government regulation to protect user privacy would be a challenge for lawmakers, and could even potentially lead to Facebook bolstering its influence.</p>
<p>What does this mean? Our individual privacy is dwindling away as we know it. The responsibility is on us to make prudent decisions regarding our social media and internet activity.</p>
<p><em>Mitchell Siegel is a Trinity sophomore. His column, “truth be told,” runs on alternate Wednesdays.</em></p>
